      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <div class="warning">
        To reduce the risk of serious injury, turn the tool off and remove the battery pack before making any
        adjustments or removing/installing attachments or accessories.
      </div>

      <h3>Cleaning</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Blow dirt and dust out of all air vents with clean, dry air at least once a week. Wear ANSI Z87.1 eye protection while doing so.</li>
        <li>Never use solvents or harsh chemicals on the non-metallic parts &mdash; they weaken the plastic. Clean with a cloth dampened only with water and mild soap.</li>
        <li>Never let liquid get inside the tool and never immerse any part of it.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Repairs &amp; service</h3>
      <p>
        To assure product safety and reliability, have repairs, maintenance and adjustment performed by a DeWalt
        factory or authorized service center, using only identical replacement parts. The charger and battery pack
        contain no serviceable parts &mdash; never service a damaged battery pack yourself.
      </p>

